10 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Montana hunters' and anglers' community fund account. (1) There is
11 a Montana hunters' and anglers' community fund account in the state special revenue fund established by 17-2-
12 102. The account is statutorily appropriated, as provided in 17-7-502, to the department of commerce. Money in
13 the account must be used by the department of commerce as provided in [section 1].
14 (2) Money transferred from any lawful source, including but not limited to donations collected
15 pursuant to [section 1], and gifts, donations, grants, securities, or other assets, public or private, must be
16 deposited in the account.
17 (3) Each year, the department of commerce may use up to 10% of the money in the account for
18 administrative costs.
19 (4) At the end of each fiscal year, any unreserved money in the account, including any interest and
20 earnings, must remain in the account.
